rk. It suggests that Heaney's translations and adaptations give a contemporary voice to medieval texts, bringing the past to bear upon contemporary concerns both personal and political. CONOR MCCARTHY gained his PhD from Trinity College Dublin.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPoetry, MedievalxAdaptationsxHistory and criticism. 0aPoetry, MedievalxTranslations into EnglishxHistory and criticism. 4aEnglish & American Literature. 4aMedieval Literature. 4aModern Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAdaptation.  aBeowulf.  aContemporary Concerns.  aLiterary Influence.  aMedieval Poetry.  aMedieval Texts.  aPoetic Tradition.  aSeamus Heaney.  aTranslation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184615605240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846156052423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846156052/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles